    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>34 Alfred Street</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>Bedford Square</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>London</placeName>
                <date>June 20/56</date>
            </p>
            <p>Rev Sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">It is my intention to<lb/> bring out a New Edition of the<lb/>
                Pentateuch and Haphtorahs in a Cheap Form</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Among the many translations<lb/> in the vernacular, other than the<lb/>
                <sic>authorised</sic> versions, your admirable<lb/> rendering takes the Palm I
                am<lb/> anxious to avail myself, with your<lb/> kind permission of your version;
                you<lb/> must be aware that there exists no<lb/> treaty of convention between the
                    <placeName>U. S.</placeName><lb/> and <placeName>England</placeName> for the
                protection<lb/> of copyright work, and can <hi rend="underline">legally</hi><lb/>
                <hi rend="underline">adopt your version</hi>; but altho I am<lb/> a very poor man I
                have too great an<lb/> appreciation of your learned and<lb/> earnest labors to rob
                you either<lb/> of your well merited fame or</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>of the material advantages which<lb/> your exertions in the cause of Hebrew<lb/>
                Literature entitle you to. I am<lb/> therefore desirous of making you<lb/> some
                equivalent, (with in my means)<lb/> on the use of your version and<lb/> name; This
                will also apply to<lb/> your version of the Sabbath Prayers</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">The form which I intend bringing out differs so materially<lb/> from
                yours as to preclude<lb/> entirely my availing myself<lb/> of any offer that you
                might<lb/> make to me with regards to your<lb/> own published work.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I await your immediate<lb/> reply informing me the sum<lb/> you
                require, for the permission<lb/> of using your name in the</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>following form.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">“The <persName>Rev. <sic>Leesers</sic></persName> version<lb/> with
                the kind permission of<lb/> the author”</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I have the honor</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">to remain</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Your Obedient Servant</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">
                <persName role="author">Philip Vallentine</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
